{"title":"Cloak of Starlight","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Cloak_of_Starlight","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.31](/0.31 \"0.31\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                        |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|   | A phosphorescent cloak, woven of pure light beams. The ripples of its folds as the wearer leaps and swerves in combat may dazzle those who gaze on it. |\n\n[![Urand starlight.png](/images/9/97/Urand_starlight.png)](/File:Urand_starlight.png) ***the +1 cloak of Starlight***\n\n+1 [cloak](/Cloak \"Cloak\")  \ncan [Dazzle](/Blind \"Blind\") attackers (20% when dodging an attack)  \n+4 [EV](/EV \"EV\")  \n[Stealth](/Stealth \"Stealth\")--\n\n## Desirability\n\nThe **cloak of Starlight**[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) is usually a very competitive piece of equipment. As a +1 cloak with +4 EV, it will be better than a mundane cloak. The [\\*Dazzle](/Blind#Dazzle \"Blind\") effect comes in handy fairly often, especially for evasive characters.\n\nThe stealth hit is generally not too painful; usually you either have enough stealth that it doesn't matter, or you aren't using stealth at all. [Stabbers](/Stab \"Stab\") might disagree when attempting to take out a sleeping [unique](/Unique \"Unique\"), but in other cases the cloak provides a lot of opportunities for low-tier stabs.\n\n## History\n\n- In [0.26](/0.26 \"0.26\"), the cloak got the \\*Dazzle property and lost rElec and rC+.\n- Prior to [0.19](/0.19 \"0.19\"), the cloak had a +2 enchantment.\n- Prior to [0.17](/0.17 \"0.17\"), the cloak had a +0 enchantment and lesser stealth penalty (Stlth-).\n- Prior to [0.15](/0.15 \"0.15\"), stealth penalty was -30.\n\n## 